commit.message: update version to 3.4.0rc

Merge pull request #1893 from knockout/1893-fix-hasfocus-ie

Setting hasFocus to false in IE clears focus from all other elements
Fix hasFocus in IE (setting hasFocus to false in IE clears focus from all other elements)

Merge pull request #1880 from knockout/1880-revert-to-jquery-parsing

Removing jQuery HTML parsing by default is breaking
Always use jQuery for HTML parsing if available, even though current versions fail with certain tags.

Merge pull request #1622 from knockout/1622-reduce-computed-notification-stack-overhead

long chains without overflowing the stack fails on FF 10-23
Switch back to using prototype method instead of closure for evaluatePossiblyAsync; reduce recursion test depth to match success result in FF.
Tweak isPureComputed implementation so it will work with subclasses too
Add ko.isPureComputed function and tests
Reduce stack overhead for recursive computed dependency notifications, especially for Firefox support (version 10-23).

Merge pull request #1866 from knockout/fix-parseHTML-on-old-IE

Fix parse html on old IE
Add missing check for allowJQueryHtmlParsing
Support all HTML parsing scenarios on all browser/library combinations that we can. This commit drops jQuery HTML parsing for all browsers except IE6-8.
Fix parseHtmlFragment on old IE, as long as you're not using jQuery or innershiv (which are still broken)
Make parseHtmlFragment tests more truthful - they should be failing on old IE
In IE, the blur method doesn't always cause the element to lose focus (for example, if the window is not in focus). Use another method to blur the element that does seem to be reliable in IE.
Fix textInput test in IE9 (see #1788)
Update test to pass in old IE; use latest version of jQuery in tests; rename function added in previous commit.
Work around fact that latest 1.x jQuery doesn't correctly parse elements like with tr-component, tbody-component, etc. Also fix issue with parsed <option> being selected in IE 8.
IE needs an element to be added to the document before it will call event handlers.

Merge pull request #1855 from massimoahmadi/patch-1

Fix for potential memory leak

Fix for potential memory leak

We detected that when we remove a component binding from the page (via a knockout if binding) then for some reason our viewModel still lives in the heap. The retainer (in the memory profiler) seems to be the "currentViewModel" variable... I wonder if it is required once the viewModel has been disposed? Because setting it to null like this seems to fix the problem and completely remove the viewModel from the heap. Is there another way this gets cleaned up that we're missing?

Merge pull request #1841 from knockout/faster-computeds

Faster computeds
A couple of style updates.
Give names to a couple of previously-anonymous functions
Reduce ko.computed evaluation overhead by about 40%
Rename getSymbolOrString to createSymbolOrString
Use Symbol to hide _state property on computeds where supported
Refactor ko.computed dispose code to reduce the number of anonymous functions (from three to one).

Clean up ko.computed code

* Remove leading underscore from "state" properties, but use it for the "state" property itself.
* Use "computed" instead of "dependentObservable" within the ko.computed code.
* Slightly simplify inheriting from ko.subscribable.
* Rename "needsEvaluation" to "isStale".
* Remove items from "state" object that aren't used by prototype methods (writeFunction and options).
* Use "notifySubscribers" within ko.computed instead of "notify" wrapper.
* Make sure "read" and "write" functions aren't called with "this = state".
